{"build_type":"executable","description":"LLM reader op.grep (structural, kind-only) with envelope. argv[1]=instruction kind (e.g. invoke_kernel_syscall, global_write, function_invocation), stdin=IPM package. Walks every function and counts matching instructions anywhere in its subtree (nested branches included), emitting {kind, hits:[{function,count}], granularity, confidence, omitted}. granularity='function-count' states IN-BAND that hits are a density-by-function summary, NOT instruction-level locations (anti-pattern #1: drill in with op.read on a listed function). confidence=exact-kind-match if any function matched, else not-found. omitted={functions_total, functions_matched}. Bad input (non-JSON / no function_definitions) -> structured error, no crash. Reuses json-tree-node, read_all_of_stdin, the stdout emitter, collect_per_function_instruction_kind_counts.","module_name":"search-instruction-classification-across-package","package_name":"search-instruction-classification-across-package","function_definitions":{"search-instruction-classification-across-package":{"return_type":"i64","parameter_definitions":[{"parameter_name":"__argc","parameter_type":"i64"},{"parameter_name":"__argv","parameter_type":"i64"}],"execution_instructions":[{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"zero","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":0},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"s_fd","variable_type":"str","assignment_operation":"string","source_target":"function_definitions"},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"s_kind","variable_type":"str","assignment_operation":"string","source_target":"kind"},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"s_hits","variable_type":"str","assignment_operation":"string","source_target":"hits"},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"s_gran","variable_type":"str","assignment_operation":"string","source_target":"granularity